  "description": [
    "750 Million Works Program to Create I Jobs Gets Senate OK The Senate has approved a 750 million emergency public works program to provide jobs in areas of heavy unemployment and has authorized an equal amount on a standby basis for use if unemployment rises A steppedup public works program has been one of _ the major legislative goals of the AFLCIO Final passage came on a 4432 vote after defeat of a number of Republican amend ments to cut back the program The Senate voted to authorize for immediate public works 150 million more than the 600 mill ion Pres Kennedy had request ed It turned down however his s request for longrun authority to divert up to 2 billion from other government programs without further appropriations to choke off a new recession The 750 million standby substitute which could be used after June 30 1963 whenever unemployment rises 1 percent within nine months and is above 5 percent requires the money to be specifically ap propriated by Congress before it can be spent Administration leaders drop ped their fight for the full long range authority requested by Kennedy when it became appar ent that the measure faced de"
  ],
